<section class="splash">
    {{> nav}}

    <div class="splash-content l-wrap">
        <h1 class="tagline">Internationalize your web apps on the client &amp; server.</h1>

        <div class="splash-example-container">
            {{{examples.splash}}}
        </div>

        <p class="splash-cta">
            <a class="splash-cta-button pure-button" href="{{pathTo 'guide'}}">
                Get Started
            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="standards docs">
    <div class="l-wrap">
        <h2>Built on standards.</h2>

        <p>
            FormatJS is aligned with: <a href="http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-402/1.0/">ECMAScript Internationalization API</a> (ECMA-402), <a href="http://userguide.icu-project.org/formatparse/messages">ICU Message</a>, and <a href="http://cldr.unicode.org/">CLDR</a> standards. By building on these standards, this project leverages APIs that exist in modern browsers, and works with the message syntax used by professional translators.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="integrations docs">
    <div class="l-wrap">
        <h2>Integrates with other libraries.</h2>

        {{> integrations-list}}

        <p>
            For most projects, localization happens in the template or view layer. FormatJS integrates with common template and component libraries by providing a single {{code "<script>"}} that you can add to your project's HTML, or {{code "require()"}} in Node.js.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="features docs">
    <div class="l-wrap">
        <h2>Formats numbers, dates, and complex messages.</h2>

        <h3 class="subheading">
            Show numbers with correct thousands and decimal separators.
        </h3>

        <p class="features-ex">
            <code class="features-ex-input">1000.95</code>
            <img class="features-ex-transform" src="/img/arrow-right.svg">
            <span class="features-ex-output">
              {{#intl locales="en-US"}}
                <i class="features-ex-locale">English</i>
                <b>{{formatNumber 1000.95}}</b>
              {{/intl}}
            </span>
            <span class="features-ex-output">
              {{#intl locales="fr-FR"}}
                <i class="features-ex-locale">French</i>
                <b>{{formatNumber 1000.95}}</b>
              {{/intl}}
            </span>
        </p>

        <h2>Modular, and ready to use.</h2>

        <h2>Runs in the browser and Node.js.</h2>
    </div>
</section>
